    <fr:title text="Image of a function">Image of a function</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be an arbitrary function. The <fr:em><fr:strong>image</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> in defined to be the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Im}(f)\subseteq  B]]></fr:tex> spanned by the values of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \mathrm {Im}(f) = {\mathopen {}\left \{f(a)\,\middle \vert \,a\in  A\right \}\mathclose {}}
]]></fr:tex>
    <fr:p>We may at times write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m_f\colon  \mathrm {Im}(f)\hookrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> for the subset inclusion, which is an <fr:link href="jms-00MO.xml" title="Injection" addr="jms-00MO" type="local">injective function</fr:link>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
